e\n!Title\n!Peak position\n!Weeks\n!Sales\n|-\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Region\n! Date\n! Format\n! Catalogue Number \n|-\n| Japan\n| {{start date|2003|3|12}}\n| CD (Copy Control CD)\n| AVCD-17278\n|-\n| Taiwan\n| {{start date|2003|}}\n| CD (Copy Control CD)\n| AVJCD-10160\n|-\n| Hong Kong\n| {{start date|2003|3|}}\n| CD (Copy Control CD)\n| AVTCD-95676\n|-\n| Indonesia\n| {{start date|2003|}} \n| Cassette\n| AV 0370303 \n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/246497/products/504191/1/ ''A Ballads''] at [[Oricon Style]]. {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Ayumi Hamasaki}}\n\n[[Category:Ayumi Hamasaki compilation albums]]\n[[Category:2003 compilation albums]]\n[[Category:Avex Group compilation albums]]\n[[Category:Japanese-language albums]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: songs co-composer \u2192 song's co-composer (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Ballads"}
{"title_page": "List of Steven Universe episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Episodes of the Cartoon Network animated series}}\n{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent [[WP:Disruptive editing|disruptive editing]]: upgrading to indefinite after seeing length of protection log|small=yes}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Steven Universe'' episodes}}\n[[File:Steven Universe logo vector.svg|frameless|right|upright]]\n''[[Steven Universe]]'' is an American animated television series created by [[Rebecca Sugar]] for [[Cartoon Network]]. The series revolves around [[Steven Universe (character)|Steven Universe]] (voiced by [[Zach Callison]]), who protects his hometown of Beach City alongside [[Garnet (Steven Universe)|Garnet]] (voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]), [[Amethyst (Steven Universe)|Amethyst]] (voiced by [[Michaela Dietz]]) and [[Pearl (Steven Universe)|Pearl]] (voiced by [[Deedee Magno Hall]]), three magical alien guardians known as the Crystal Gems. Episodes of ''Steven Universe'' and its sequel, ''Steven Universe Future'', have variously been broadcast once a week, most recently on Friday nights, or in blocks of multiple new episodes in the course of a week, which are marketed as \"Stevenbombs\", or back-to-back as specials with an umbrella title.<ref name=\"The Guardian 12 January 2016\">{{cite news|last1=Thurm|first1=Eric|title=Steven Universe censorship undermines Cartoon Network's LGBTQ progress|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2016/jan/12/steven-universe-censorship-cartoon-networks-lgbtq|accessdate=12 January 2016|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{Aired episodes|all|title=Steven Universe|finished=all|seasons=5|num=160}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ianjq |author=Ian Jones-Quartey |number=1180164855279443969 |title=The original \"Steven Universe\" is over. This is not season 6, this is a whole new sequel/epilogue series! Can't wait for it to come out! |date=October 4, 2019 |accessdate=October 4, 2019}}</ref> A [[television film]], ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]'', was released on September 2, 2019, following the fifth and final season.<ref name=\"StevenUniverseTheMovie2019\" /> A concluding [[limited series (television)|limited series]], ''[[Steven Universe Future]]'', premiered on December 7, 2019.<ref name=\"SUF\">{{cite web|title=Steven Universe gets a new title and opening sequence for final season|url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/10/4/20892306/steven-universe-future-final-season-6-title-sequence-song|first=Petrana|last=Radulovic|website=Polygon|date=October 4, 2019|accessdate=October 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"SUFDate\">{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/tv-shows/2019/11/20/steven-universe-future-official-trailer |title=Steven Universe Future Releases First Official Trailer |work=ComicBook.com |first=Rollin |last=Bishop |date=November 20, 2019 |accessdate=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color0S      = #FA98C0\n| link0S       = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Pilot (2013)\n| linkT0S      = Pilot\n| start0S      = {{Start date|2013|5|21}}\n\n| color1       = #FF5E6D\n| link1        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2013\u201315)\n| episodes1    = 53\n| start1       = {{Start date|2013|11|4}}\n| end1         = {{End date|2015|4|16}}\n\n| color2       = #91ECDD\n| link2        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2015\u201316)\n| episodes2    = 25\n| start2       = {{Start date|2015|3|13}}\n| end2         = {{End date|2016|1|8}}\n\n| color3       = #B895D1\n| link3        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2016)\n| episodes3    = 25\n| start3       = {{Start date|2016|5|12}}\n| end3         = {{End date|2016|8|10}}\n\n| color4       = #A12766\n| link4        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2016\u201317)\n| episodes4    = 25\n| start4       = {{Start date|2016|8|11}}\n| end4         = {{End date|2017|5|11}}\n\n| color5       = #ACDF7D\n| link5        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2017\u201319)\n| episodes5    = 32\n| start5       = {{Start date|2017|5|29}}\n| end5         = {{End date|2019|1|21}}\n\n| color5SA     = #FF668F\n| link5SA      = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Film (2019)\n| linkT5SA     = Film\n| start5SA     = {{Start date|2019|9|2}}\n| color5SB     = #74D5F3\n\n| link5SB      = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Steven Universe Future (2019\u201320)\n| episodes5SB  = 20\n| linkT5SB     = ''Future''\n| start5SB     = {{Start date|2019|12|7}}\n| end5SB       = {{End date|2020|3|27}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\nThe order and length of the first three seasons is inconsistent between official sources; this list uses the \"intended order\" of the episodes as specified by Ian Jones-Quartey, which re-orders six episodes from the first two seasons compared to the broadcast order.<ref name=\"intended order\">{{Cite web|last=Jones-Quartey|first=Ian|authorlink=Ian Jones-Quartey|date=July 12, 2015|title=The Intended Order|url=http://ianjq.tumblr.com/post/123939657564/now-that-all-the-season-1-episodes-are-out-could|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721032303/http://ianjq.tumblr.com/post/123939657564/now-that-all-the-season-1-episodes-are-out-could|archivedate=July 21, 2015|accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Pilot (2013)===\n{{Episode table |background=#FA98C9 |title=27 |director=16 |writer=29 |airdate=28 |released=y |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| Title           = The Time Thing\n| RTitle          = <ref name=\"artbook\">{{cite book|last=McDonnell|first=Chris|date=2017|title=''Steven Universe'': Art & Origins|publisher=Harry N. Abrams|page=238|isbn=1419724436}}</ref>\n| DirectedBy      = Phil Rynda {{small|(creative)}}, Sue Mondt {{small|(art)}}, and [[Genndy Tartakovsky]] {{small|([[Timing (animation)|timing]])}}\n| WrittenBy       = [[Rebecca Sugar]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|5|21}}{{refn|group=nb|name=pilot|The pilot was first released online, and the air date shows when the pilot was released online.}}\n| ShortSummary    = Upon returning from an intergalactic mission, the Crystal Gems\u2014Garnet, Amethyst, and Pearl\u2014have brought a mysterious magical hourglass. Steven Universe, the youngest member of the Crystal Gems, gets his hands on the device and discovers that it has the ability to let him travel back in time in order to make snappy comebacks. However, his actions soon bring about a deadly adversary, with everyone's lives dependent on Steven being able to make a worthwhile comeback.\n| LineColor       = FA98C9\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2013\u201315)===\n* Episode premieres initially occurred weekly on Monday nights.\n* Episode premieres moved to Wednesday nights beginning with the episode \"Steven the Sword Fighter\".\n* Episode premieres moved again to Thursday nights beginning with the episode \"Coach Steven\". \n* The episodes \"Open Book\", \"Shirt Club\", and \"Story for Steven\" were bumped to air during the second season in order to facilitate airing the final 'arc' of season one over five consecutive nights.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Burnett|first=Matt|date=March 8, 2015|title=For those who are letting this distract them from enjoying the #StevenBomb|url=http://matt-burnett.tumblr.com/post/113119840091/for-those-who-are-letting-this-distract-them-from|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150311155804/http://matt-burnett.tumblr.com/post/113119840091/for-those-who-are-letting-this-distract-them-from|archivedate=March 11, 2015|accessdate=October 29, 2018}}</ref>\n*The episode \"Say Uncle\" was produced and aired as part of the second season, as denoted by its different production code. It chronologically occurs late in the first season, and as such is listed here.<ref name=\"intended order\"/>\n{{Episode table |background=#FF5E6D |overall=5 |season=5 |title=17 |director=16 |writer=29 |airdate=12 |prodcode=6 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = [[Gem Glow]]\n| DirectedBy      = [[Ian Jones-Quartey]] {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Kevin Dart {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Joe Johnston and Jeff Liu\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|11|4}}\n| ProdCode        = 1020-003\n| Viewers         = 1.86<ref name=\"Anon. 2013a\">{{Cite web|date=November 5, 2013 |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/11/05/mondays-cable-ratings-and-broadcast-finals-mnf-trumps-voice-in-demos-viewers-350113/cable_20131104/ |title=Monday's Cable Ratings & Broadcast Finals: ''MNF'' Trumps ''Voice'' in Demos, Viewers |work=[[The Futon Critic]] |publisher=Futon Media |archiveurl=https://timetravel.mementoweb.org/memento/20131106034411/http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/11/05/mondays-cable-ratings-and-broadcast-finals-mnf-trumps-voice-in-demos-viewers-350113/cable_20131104/ |archivedate=November 6, 2013 |accessdate=November 5, 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Steven is disappointed that his favorite ice-cream sandwich brand, Cookie Cat, gets taken off the market. He soon cheers up upon discovering that the Gems managed to get hold of some of the last remaining Cookie Cats, which he comes to believe may be the key to activating his gem.\n| LineColor       = FF5E6D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Laser Light Cannon\n| DirectedBy      = Ian Jones-Quartey {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Kevin Dart {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Kat Morris and [[Rebecca Sugar]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|11|4}}\n| ProdCode        = 1020-001\n| Viewers         = 1.86<ref name=\"Anon. 2013a\" />\n| ShortSummary    = When a menacing \"Red Eye\" is about to hit Beach City, the 