y through their ancient Crystal Temple; but when the breakfast absorbs a dangerous artifact, it comes to life and must be defeated.\n| LineColor       = FF5E6D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = Frybo\n| DirectedBy      = Ian Jones-Quartey {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Kevin Dart {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Raven M. Molisee and Paul Villeco\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|11|18}}\n| ProdCode        = 1020-008\n| Viewers         = 1.29<ref name=\"Anon. 2013c\">{{Cite news|date=November 19, 2013|title=Monday Cable Finals|publisher=[[Nielsen Media Research]]}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Steven brings a mascot costume to life with a magical gem shard in order to help his friend Peedee, but it backfires when the mascot goes rogue.\n| LineColor       = FF5E6D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = Cat Fingers\n| DirectedBy      = Ian Jones-Quartey {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Kevin Dart {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Kat Morris, Hilary Florido, Ian Jones-Quartey and Rebecca Sugar\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|11|25}}\n| ProdCode        = 1020-005\n| Viewers         = 1.71<ref name=\"Anon. 2013d\">{{Cite web|date=November 26, 2013 |url=http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/11/26/mondays-cable-ratings-and-broadcast-finals-mnf-voice-lead-demos-dwts-tops-viewers-259311/cable_20131125/ |title=Monday's Cable Ratings & Broadcast Finals: ''MNF'', ''Voice'' Lead Demos; ''DWTS'' Tops Viewers |work=[[The Futon Critic]] |publisher=Futon Media |archiveurl=https://timetravel.mementoweb.org/memento/20131127005656/http://thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2013/11/26/mondays-cable-ratings-and-broadcast-finals-mnf-voice-lead-demos-dwts-tops-viewers-259311/cable_20131125/ |archivedate=November 27, 2013 |accessdate=November 26, 2013 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Trying to master his shapeshifting abilities, Steven turns his fingers into cats, which 