"Legs from Here to Homeworld\", \"Familiar\", \"Together Alone\", \"Escapism\", and \"Change Your Mind\" aired as a five-week special event titled ''Diamond Days''.\n\n{{Episode table |background=#ACDF7D |overall=5 |season=5 |title=17 |director=16 |writer=29 |airdate=12 |prodcode=6 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 129\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = Stuck Together\n| RTitle          = {{small| (Part 1)}}\n| DirectedBy      = Kat Morris {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Liz Artinian {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Lauren Zuke\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|5|29}}<br />{{refn|group=nb|name=online3|This episode was first released online on May 10, 2017.}}\n| ProdCode        = 1053-133\n| Viewers         = 1.53<ref name=\"showbuzzdaily.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-29-2017.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals&nbsp;& Network Finals: 5.29.2017 - Showbuzz Daily|website=showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 31, 2017}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Steven and Lars, stuck inside Topaz, try to look for a way to escape the Homeworld-bound ship. Their heartfelt conversation commiserating over their plight earns them Topaz's sympathy.\n| LineColor       = ACDF7D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 130\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = The Trial\n| RTitle          = {{small| (Part 2)}}\n| DirectedBy      = Joe Johnston {{small|(supervising)}}<br />Liz Artinian {{small|(art)}}\n| WrittenBy       = Katie Mitroff and Paul Villeco\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|5|29}}\n| ProdCode        = 1053-134\n| Viewers         = 1.53<ref name=\"showbuzzdaily.com\"/>\n| ShortSummary    = Steven is put on trial before Blue and Yellow Diamond for Rose Quartz's assassination of Pink Diamond. During the trial, Steven's attorney, a Zircon, analyses the evidence and argues that th