Steven Universe: The Movie Release Date |work=Digital Spy |first=Alec |last=Bojalad |date=January 21, 2019 |accessdate=January 22, 2019}}</ref> its production was first announced on July 21, 2018, at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] with the release of its first [[teaser campaign|teaser]] trailer.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Patches |first1=Matt |title=Steven Universe movie announcement, teaser surprises at SDCC |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/21/17597892/steven-universe-the-movie-trailer-sdcc-2018 |accessdate=21 July 2018 |work=Polygon}}</ref> The film is a [[Musical film|musical]], featuring musical collaborations with [[Chance the Rapper]], [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]], [[Gallant (singer)|Gallant]], [[Aimee Mann]], [[James Fauntleroy]], [[Macie Stewart]], [[Mike Krol]], and others,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haring |first1=Bruce |title='Steven Universe The Movie' Adds Chance The Rapper, Patti LuPone And More To Musical |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/steven-universe-the-movie-chance-the-rapper-patti-lupone-cartoon-network-1202631825/ |accessdate=June 13, 2019 |work=Deadline |date=June 13, 2019}}</ref> and takes place two years after the events of \"Change Your Mind\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ydJrPHK2Db8|title=Steven's New Neck {{!}} Steven Universe The Movie {{!}} Cartoon Network|website=YouTube|publisher=Cartoon Network|date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |background=#FF668F |title=27 |director=16 |writer=29 |airdate=12 |prodcode=6 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| RTitle          = ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]''\n| DirectedBy      = [[Rebecca Sugar]]<br />Kat Morris and Joe Johnston {{small|(co-directors)}}\n| WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Matt Burnett, Ben Levin, Hilary Florido, Kat Morris, Rebecca Sugar, Joe Johnston, [[Ian Jones-Quartey]] and Jack Pendarvis|ex1label=Written and storyboarded by|ex1=Lamar Abrams, Hilary Florido, Kat Morris, Miki Brewster, Joe Johnston, Chris Pianka, Amber Cragg, Amish Kumar, Madeline Queripel, Jeff Liu, Rebecca Sugar, Katie Mitroff and Paul Villeco}}\n| ProdCode        = 1076-000\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|2}}\n| Viewers         = 1.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-2-2019.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.2.2019|first=Mitch|last=Metcalf|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Two years after the events of \"Change Your Mind\", Steven thinks he has earned a happy ending after reforming the Gem Empire. However, Earth is attacked by a Gem named Spinel, a former playmate of Pink Diamond's come to take revenge on Steven for his mother abandoning her. Spinel erases Garnet, Amethyst and Pearl's memories and begins poisoning the planet. In a race against time, Steven must find a way to restore their memories and deactivate Spinel's poison injector before all organic life on Earth is destroyed.\n| LineColor       = FF668F\n}}\n}}\n\n==''Steven Universe Future'' (2019\u201320)==\n{{anchor|Steven Universe Future}}\n{{main|Steven Universe Future}}\nA [[limited series (television)|limited series]], ''Steven Universe Future'', intended to serve as an epilogue to the main series, premiered on December 7, 2019.<ref name=\"SUFDate\" />\n{{:Steven Universe Future}}\n\n==Shorts==\n===Season 2 (2015)===\nAll six digital shorts combined make up one full production code of the second season (1031-058).<ref>{{Cite web|author=Burnett, Matt (@mcburnett)|date=August 1, 2016|url=https://twitter.com/mcburnett/status/760165779786444800|title=Bismuth (airing Thursday) is the 100th SU episode because all digital shorts made up an episode...}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |background=#91ECDD |overall=5 |title=38 |writer=41 |airdate=16 |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumb