053/steven-universe-arcade-mania|title=Steven Universe Arcade Mania|website=Madman Entertainment|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815120107/https://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/35053/steven-universe-arcade-mania|archivedate=August 15, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Region 2===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Title\n! Episode count\n! Running time (minutes)\n! Episodes\n! Extra features\n! Release date\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF5E6D\" |\n| ''Season One''\n| 52\n| 572\n| | 1\u201335, 37, 36, 38-47, 49-53{{refn|group=nb|name=UKBD|The packaging for this release incorrectly uses the same episodes listing as the American Season One DVD.}}\n| Pilot episode, ''Behind the Music'' and ''Listening Party'' featurettes,<br>video performances and early demos of songs, animatics\n| February 24, 2020<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Manga Entertainment |author-link=Manga Entertainment |user=MangaUK |number=1222891607961128965 |date=30 January 2020 |title=Steven Universe: Season One will now be released on 24/02|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n; Production code columns\n* Production codes are stamped on numerous model sheets and storyboards that must be searched for, in: {{Cite web|author=Steven Crewniverse|url=http://stevencrewniverse.tumblr.com/archive|title=''Steven Crewniverse Behind-the-Scenes Universe'': Archive|accessdate=November 5, 2014}} http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/shows/steven-universe/pictures/index.html\n\n{{Steven Universe}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Steven Universe episodes, List of}}\n[[Category:2010s television-related lists]]\n[[Category:Cartoon Network-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of American children's animated television series episodes]]\n[[Category:Steven Universe episodes| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Episodes of the Cartoon Network animated series}}\n{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent [[WP:Disruptive editing|disruptive editing]]: upgrading to indefinite after seeing length of protection log|small=yes}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Steven Universe'' episodes}}\n[[File:Steven Universe logo vector.svg|frameless|right|upright]]\n''[[Steven Universe]]'' is an American animated television series created by [[Rebecca Sugar]] for [[Cartoon Network]]. The series revolves around [[Steven Universe (character)|Steven Universe]] (voiced by [[Zach Callison]]), who protects his hometown of Beach City alongside [[Garnet (Steven Universe)|Garnet]] (voiced by [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]]), [[Amethyst (Steven Universe)|Amethyst]] (voiced by [[Michaela Dietz]]) and [[Pearl (Steven Universe)|Pearl]] (voiced by [[Deedee Magno Hall]]), three magical alien guardians known as the Crystal Gems. Episodes of ''Steven Universe'' and its sequel, ''Steven Universe Future'', have variously been broadcast once a week, most recently on Friday nights, or in blocks of multiple new episodes in the course of a week, which are marketed as \"Stevenbombs\", or back-to-back as specials with an umbrella title.<ref name=\"The Guardian 12 January 2016\">{{cite news|last1=Thurm|first1=Eric|title=Steven Universe censorship undermines Cartoon Network's LGBTQ progress|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2016/jan/12/steven-universe-censorship-cartoon-networks-lgbtq|accessdate=12 January 2016|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{Aired episodes|all|title=Steven Universe|finished=all|seasons=5|num=160}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=ianjq |author=Ian Jones-Quartey |number=1180164855279443969 |title=The original \"Steven Universe\" is over. This is not season 6, this is a whole new sequel/epilogue series! Can't wait for it to come out! |date=October 4, 2019 |accessdate=October 4, 2019}}</ref> A [[television film]], ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]'', was released on September 2, 2019, following the fifth and final season.<ref name=\"StevenUniverseTheMovie2019\" /> A concluding [[limited series (television)|limited series]], ''[[Steven Universe Future]]'', premiered on December 7, 2019.<ref name=\"SUF\">{{cite web|title=Steven Universe gets a new title and opening sequence for final season|url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/10/4/20892306/steven-universe-future-final-season-6-title-sequence-song|first=Petrana|last=Radulovic|website=Polygon|date=October 4, 2019|accessdate=October 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"SUFDate\">{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/tv-shows/2019/11/20/steven-universe-future-official-trailer |title=Steven Universe Future Releases First Official Trailer |work=ComicBook.com |first=Rollin |last=Bishop |date=November 20, 2019 |accessdate=November 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color0S      = #FA98C0\n| link0S       = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Pilot (2013)\n| linkT0S      = Pilot\n| start0S      = {{Start date|2013|5|21}}\n\n| color1       = #FF5E6D\n| link1        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2013\u201315)\n| episodes1    = 53\n| start1       = {{Start date|2013|11|4}}\n| end1         = {{End date|2015|4|16}}\n\n| color2       = #91ECDD\n| link2        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2015\u201316)\n| episodes2    = 25\n| start2       = {{Start date|2015|3|13}}\n| end2         = {{End date|2016|1|8}}\n\n| color3       = #B895D1\n| link3        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2016)\n| episodes3    = 25\n| start3       = {{Start date|2016|5|12}}\n| end3         = {{End date|2016|8|10}}\n\n| color4       = #A12766\n| link4        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2016\u201317)\n| episodes4    = 25\n| start4       = {{Start date|2016|8|11}}\n| end4         = {{End date|2017|5|11}}\n\n| color5       = #ACDF7D\n| link5        = <includeonly>List of Steven Universe episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2017\u201319)