018, at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] with the release of its first [[teaser campaign|teaser]] trailer.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Patches |first1=Matt |title=Steven Universe movie announcement, teaser surprises at SDCC |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/21/17597892/steven-universe-the-movie-trailer-sdcc-2018 |accessdate=21 July 2018 |work=Polygon}}</ref> The film is a [[Musical film|musical]], featuring musical collaborations with [[Chance the Rapper]], [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]], [[Gallant (singer)|Gallant]], [[Aimee Mann]], [[James Fauntleroy]], [[Macie Stewart]], [[Mike Krol]], and others,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haring |first1=Bruce |title='Steven Universe The Movie' Adds Chance The Rapper, Patti LuPone And More To Musical |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/steven-universe-the-movie-chance-the-rapper-patti-lupone-cartoon-network-1202631825/ |accessdate=June 13, 2019 |work=Deadline |date=June 13, 2019}}</ref> and takes place two years after the events of \"Change Your Mind\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ydJrPHK2Db8|title=Steven's New Neck {{!}} Steven Universe The Movie {{!}} Cartoon Network|website=YouTube|publisher=Cartoon Network|date=July 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |background=#FF668F |title=27 |director=16 |writer=29 |airdate=12 |prodcode=6 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| RTitle          = ''[[Steven Universe: The Movie]]''\n| DirectedBy      = [[Rebecca Sugar]]<br />Kat Morris and Joe Johnston {{small|(co-directors)}}\n| WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Matt Burnett, Ben Levin, Hilary Florido, Kat Morris, Rebecca Sugar, Joe Johnston, [[Ian Jones-Quartey]] and Jack Pendarvis|ex1label=Written and storyboarded by|ex1=Lamar Abrams, Hilary Florido, Kat Morris, Miki Brewster, Joe Johnston, Chris Pianka, Amber Cragg, Amish Kumar, Madeline Queripel, Jeff Liu, Rebecca Sugar, Katie Mitroff and Paul Villeco}}\n| ProdCode        = 1076-000\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|2}}\n| Viewers         = 1.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-2-2019.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.2.2019|first=Mitch|last=Metcalf|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Two years after the events of \"Change Your Mind\", Steven thinks he has earned a happy ending after reforming the Gem Empire. However, Earth is attacked by a Gem named Spinel, a former playmate of Pink Diamond's come to take revenge on Steven for his mother abandoning her. Spinel erases Garnet, Amethyst and Pearl's memories and begins poisoning the planet. In a race against time, Steven must find a way to restore their memories and deactivate Spinel's poison injector before all organic life on Earth is destroyed.\n| LineColor       = FF668F\n}}\n}}\n\n==''Steven Universe Future'' (2019\u201320)==\n{{anchor|Steven Universe Future}}\n{{main|Steven Universe Future}}\nA [[limited series (television)|limited series]], ''Steven Universe Future'', intended to serve as an epilogue to the main series, premiered on December 7, 2019.<ref name=\"SUFDate\" />\n{{:Steven Universe Future}}\n\n==Shorts==\n===Season 2 (2015)===\nAll six digital shorts combined make up one full production code of the second season (1031-058).<ref>{{Cite web|author=Burnett, Matt (@mcburnett)|date=August 1, 2016|url=https://twitter.com/mcburnett/status/760165779786444800|title=Bismuth (airing Thursday) is the 100th SU episode because all digital shorts made up an episode...}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |background=#91ECDD |overall=5 |title=38 |writer=41 |airdate=16 |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Lion Loves to Fit in a Box\n| WrittenBy       = Katie Mitroff\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|5|28}}\n| ShortSummary    = Lion unsuccessfully attempts to get into various boxes.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = What Are Gems?\n| WrittenBy       = Hilary Florido\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|7|6}}\n| ShortSummary    = Pearl teaches Steven about Gems, with some demonstrations from Garnet and Amethyst.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = We Are the Crystal Gems\n| WrittenBy       = Hilary Florido, Joe Johnston, Jeff Liu and Katie Mitroff\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|9|4}}{{refn|group=nb|name=Crystalgems|This short was first shown during the ''Steven Universe'' panel at [[San Diego Comic-Con]] on July 10, 2015.}}\n| ShortSummary    = Young Steven moves in with the three Crystal Gems, as the extended version of the title theme and second opening sequence shows.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = How Are Gems Made?\n| WrittenBy       = Hilary Florido\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = Amethyst tells Steven how Gems are made.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = Unboxing\n| WrittenBy       = Hilary Florido and Katie Mitroff\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|22}}\n| ShortSummary    = Steven creates a video where he receives and unboxes a new Hot Dog duffel bag from the Wacky Sack company.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = Fusion\n| WrittenBy       = Katie Mitroff\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|11|2}}\n| ShortSummary    = Garnet takes over a dance studio to demonstrate to Steven how fusion works.\n| LineColor       = 91ECDD\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 4 (2016)===\nAll five of these shorts combined make up one full production code of the fourth season (1040-112).<ref>{{Cite web|author=Turner Classic all 5 of these shorts will make a full episode of season 4 Movies|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/person/12875701%7C0/Zach-Callison/filmography.html|title=Zach Callison Filmography|accessdate=August 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |background=#A12766 |overall=5 |title=38 |writer=41 |airdate=16 |writerT=Written and storyboarded by |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Cooking with Lion\n| WrittenBy       = Colin Howard\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary    = Steven and Lion make [[cheese puff]] snack [[sushi]] for their online cooking show. Lion eats the dish at the end of the episode.\n| LineColor       = A12766\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Gem Karaoke\n| WrittenBy       = Colin Howard\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary    = Connie records Steven and the Gems singing karaoke. Connie is reluctant to participate, but Steven convinces her to join in for the final verse.\n| LineColor       = A12766\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = Steven Reacts\n| WrittenBy       = Jeff Liu\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary    = Steven films a [[reaction video]] to the new episode of ''Crying Breakfast Friends''. The events of the ''Crying Breakfast Friends'' episode and Steven's reactions humorously draw parallels to events in ''Steven Universe'' itself and fan reactions.\n| LineColor       = A12766\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = Video Chat\n| WrittenBy       = Colin Howard\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary    = On Connie's laptop, Steven video chats with Peridot on her tablet. Lapis, however, believes him to be trapped in the tablet. Steven rushes to the barn to explain.\n| LineColor       = A12766\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = Steven's Song Time\n| WrittenBy       = Jeff Liu\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary    = Steven makes a guitar tutorial for a song he comp