itle=Steven Universe Season 1 (Blu-Ray)|website=Madman Entertainment|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427214826/http://www.madman.com.au/catalogue/view/35879/steven-universe-season-1-bluray|archivedate=April 27, 2016|df=}}</ref> [[Manga Entertainment]] released the first season in the United Kingdom, using content from Madman's release;<ref name=\"Manga UK 1\">{{cite web |last1=A. Stevens |first1=Josh |title=Manga UK to release Goblin Slayer, Fruits Basket and more! |url=https://animeuknews.net/2019/08/manga-uk-to-release-goblin-slayer-fruits-basket-and-more/ |website=Anime UK News |accessdate=2 August 2019 |date=2 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |author=Manga Entertainment |author-link=Manga Entertainment |user=MangaUK |number=1157292832358633472 |date=2 August 2019 |title=we will be receiving our Steven Universe content from Madman |access-date=2 August 2019}}</ref> a release of the second season was planned for March 16, 2020, but was cancelled before release.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Manga Entertainment |author-link=Manga Entertainment |user=MangaUK |number=1235232006147100673 |date=2 August 2019 |title=Due to unforeseen circumstances, we are unfortunately no longer able to release the previously announced Steven Universe Season 2. |access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSeveral episodes are re-ordered on home video. In the table below, the episodes are listed in the order they appear on the disc, and are numbered according to the [[#Episodes|episode tables above]].\n\n===Region 1===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Title\n! Episode count\n! Running time (minutes)\n! Episodes\n! Extra features\n! Release date\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Season releases\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FF5E6D\" |\n| ''The Complete First Season''\n| 52\n| 572\n| 1\u201346, 50\u201355\n| ''Behind the Music'' and ''Listening Party'' featurettes,<br>video performances and early demos of songs, animatics<ref>{{cite news |las